+# PR-214 Remediation Report
+
+## Thread Triage
+
+- `T-214-01`: actionable
+- `T-214-02`: duplicate of `T-214-01`
+- `T-214-03`: obsolete
+- `T-214-04`: actionable
+- `T-214-05`: actionable
+
+The triage source of truth is `.github/review_export/pr_214_threads.json`. `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md` was treated as stale scratch context only.
+
+## Remediation Applied
+
+- Updated `src/policy/approval_router.py` so `build_policy_preview(...)` normalizes approval states before calling the preview payload builder.
+- Updated `src/policy/preview.py` so the fallback payload keeps `approval_state` and `requires_human_review` when preview rendering is unavailable.
+- Updated `tests/test_preview.py` with regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` and `approval_state="manual_review"`, asserting the normalized fallback result is `human_review_required` with `requires_human_review=true`.
+- Updated `docs/approval_policy.md` to show the corrected fallback payload.
+
+## Intentional Non-Changes
+
+- Did not apply `T-214-02` separately because it duplicates `T-214-01`.
+- Did not apply `T-214-03` because it targets an outdated hunk and would reintroduce legacy behavior.
+- Did not modify `.github/review_export/`, `artifacts/review/thread_digest.md`, `tests/test_approval_router.py`, `AGENTS.md`, `Dockerfile`, `.scenario_variant`, `release_context/`, or `incident_context/`.
+- Did not add `legacy_preview_hint`.
+
+## Verification
+
+- Ran `python3 -m unittest tests.test_preview tests.test_approval_router`
+- Result: `Ran 5 tests in 0.000s` and `OK`
+
+## Outcome
+
+`build_policy_preview(request_id=..., approval_state="manual_review", preview_enabled=False, actor=...)` now returns a fallback payload that preserves:
+
+```json
+{
+  "request_id": "req-214",
+  "status": "preview_unavailable",
+  "actor": "review-bot",
+  "approval_state": "human_review_required",
+  "requires_human_review": true
+}
+```
