+# PR-214 Reply Draft
+
+## T-214-01
+
+Fixed in `src/policy/preview.py` and `src/policy/approval_router.py`. The fallback payload now preserves `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`, and the router normalizes `manual_review` to `human_review_required` before building either preview variant.
+
+## T-214-02
+
+Marked duplicate of `T-214-01`. No separate code change was applied because it reports the same reopened fallback payload regression.
+
+## T-214-03
+
+Not applied. This thread is obsolete on the current branch because it points at an outdated diff hunk and would revive legacy preview behavior that should stay removed.
+
+## T-214-04
+
+Addressed in `tests/test_preview.py`. Added regression coverage for `preview_enabled=False` with `approval_state="manual_review"` and asserted the normalized fallback payload keeps `approval_state="human_review_required"` plus `requires_human_review=true`.
+
+## T-214-05
+
+Addressed in `docs/approval_policy.md`. The fallback response example now shows the corrected payload, including `approval_state` and `requires_human_review`.
